text: The Fremont Building is a historic commercial building located at 3419 Fremont Avenue North in Seattle, Washington. The two-story building, built in the late 19th and 20th century Revival style, was completed in 1911 and added to the National Register of Historic Places on November 12, 1992. The building currently houses a vintage store. ==See also== * National Register of Historic Places listings in Seattle, Washington ==References== ==External links== * Category:1910s architecture in the United States Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1911 Category:National Register of Historic Places in Seattle
